original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 code to render green terminal text uses the ANSI escape sequence for setting the foreground color to green. In this case, the appropriate code is "\033[32m", where "\033" represents the escape character, "[", followed by "32", another closing bracket, and finally "m". This combination instructs the terminal emulator to display subsequent text in green color.

Here's an example demonstrating its usage:

```
\033[32mHello, Green Terminal! \033[0m
```

In the given example, "Hello, Green Terminal!" will appear in green color within the terminal. Note that "\033[0m" resets the formatting back to default, ensuring only the specified portion appears colored. Remember that the effectiveness of this solution depends on whether your terminal emulator supports ANSI escape codes. If unsure, consult your terminal's documentation or preferences to enable support for ANSI escape codes.
